data-triple-N3.o: "In mathematics, a real number is a value that represents a quantity along a continuous line. The real numbers include all the rational numbers, such as the integer 5 and the fraction 4/3, and all the irrational numbers such as 2 and . Real numbers can be thought of as points on an infinitely long line called the number line or real line, where the points corresponding to integers are equally spaced."@en
